# How to Report Fraudulent Card Transactions (Adyen)

## Overview

We have a defined procedure for collecting and processing dispute requests. Please follow these steps to ensure requests are handled quickly and successfully.

- CSV template & instructions:  
  https://www.notion.so/uselight/How-to-report-Fraudulent-Card-Transactions-Adyen-2cdf9bd84c8c802b82a3c9644a136b42?source=copy_link

- Attached files:
  - `disputes.csv` (template)
  - `Disputes_Form_(Fraud).docx` (optional evidence template)

This CSV format is required for:
- Fraud disputes
- Goods/Services not delivered
- Duplicate disputes

Other dispute types must be submitted via Adyen Support.

> Note: The Disputes API exists but is **not currently supported**.

---

## Eligibility

- Only **captured** payments can be disputed
- Cannot dispute:
  - authorised
  - cancelled
  - expired
  - refunded
- Disputes must be submitted within **120 days of capture**

---

